  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature request.\r\nFor a use case when we want to show custom validation message, or use Material-ui style of floating label , it's necessary to know that there is an actual value in the input\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nCurrently, if the manual date entry is incorrect, the onChange is called with a 'null'\r\nhttps://github.com/airbnb/react-dates/blob/master/src/components/SingleDatePicker.jsx#L189\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nallow exposing of current display value in a callback.\r\nAs options that I can think of: provide bool flag \"allowInvalidInCallback\" and return an object of let's say\r\n`{\r\nvalue: '01/02/',\r\nerror: 'wrong format',\r\n}\r\n`\r\nor \r\n`\r\n {\r\nvalue: '01/02/2018',\r\nerror: 'selected date is disabled'\r\n}\r\n`\r\nIs that feasible? \r\n",
